THE owner of Enyobeni tavern together with two employees aged between 33 and 34 were arrested over the weekend and on Tuesday, 12 July respectively for contravention of the Liquor Act. Enyobeni tavern in Scenery Park in East London is where 21 children between 13 and 22 years died from a yet-to-be-determined cause. The teens were buried in a mass funeral last Wednesday 06 July, at Scenery Park Sports Field. ALSO READ: Tecno’s a quality player! The arrest comes after the Eastern Cape Liquor Board laid charges for contravention of the Liquor Act. An R2000 fine was issued to each of the two tavern employees, whilst summons were served to the owner for his immediate arrest and appearance in the court of law. The tavern owner is expected in the East London magistrates court on the 19 August 2022 and the two employees have been given an option of a fine in terms of the Liquor Act.